FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - ECUADOR (05): OIE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 7 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, 6 Jul 2006, Vol. 19 - No. 27 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_11.HTM#Sec9>

Foot & mouth disease in Ecuador: Follow-up report No. 1
Translation of information received on 4 Jul 2006 from Dr Gustavo F.
Mino Verdesoto, Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock, Department of
Animal Health Emergency and Epidemiological Surveillance, Quito:
End of previous report period: 25 May 2006 (see Disease Information,
19 [22], 425, dated 1 Jun 2006).
End of this report period: 4 Jul 2006.
Identification of agent: foot and mouth disease virus serotype O.
Date of start of the event: 15 May 2006.
New outbreak: A new outbreak was reported from a farm in Pichincha
province, Pedro Vicente Maldonado on 15 May 2006. There were 32
susceptible animals including 4 cases.
<http://www.oie.int/cartes/19_27_ECU_A.doc>
Description of affected population: 3 calves and a young bull in a
small farm principally involved in milk production.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: National Veterinary
Laboratory Izquieta Perez
Results: complement fixation test on 14 Jun 2006 were positive.
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: fomites.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This appears to be very close to the 1st outbreak in Santo Domingo
-- see below. For another map, see
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/EC/18/Pedro_Vicente_Maldonado.html> - Mod.PC]
